Billionaire Lauder Forms Moscow Hotel Venture, Vedomosti Reports

-- B y   Y u l i a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-03-24T05:41:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/billionaire-lauder-forms-moscow-hotel-venture-vedomosti-reports.html
U.S. billionaire Ronald Lauder, a
shareholder in cosmetics maker Estee Lauder Cos., invested about
12 billion rubles ($423 million) for a stake in a hotel venture
with Moscow’s city government, Vedomosti reported.  Lauder will have 20 percent of the Gostinichnaya venture,
which will control the city’s stakes in 15 hotels in the Russian
capital, including the Hotel Moskva near Red Square, the
newspaper said today, citing unidentified city officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
